OpenTTD includes an in-game tutorial that guides you through the interface. It covers mucht the same as the beginner tutorial on the wiki, but is programmed as an interactive in-game tutorial. Follow the steps below to download and start the tutorial.

=== Chapters ===
The in-game beginner tutorial contains these chapters:
<ol start="0">
<li>Introduction
<li>Navigation
<li>Aircraft
<li>Ships
<li>Trucks and industry chains
<li>Buses and town growth
<li>''Rail (incomplete)''</ol>

=== How to get and start the Tutorial ===
1. Click on Play Scenario (in the main menu).

[[File:en/Manual/Tutorial/Main menu play scenario.png]]


2. Click on the Check Online Content button (lower left).

[[File:en/Manual/Tutorial/Load scenario check online.png]]


3. Download the "Beginner Tutorial". Use the filter if you want to restrict the list of content.

[[File:en/Manual/Tutorial/Download tutorial.png]]


4. Close the download window.

6. Select the "Beginner Tutorial" in the Load Scenario window.

7. If you get a red text about missing files, click on the "find missing content online" button and download the NewGRF file required by the tutorial.

8. Click on "Load".

[[File:en/Manual/Tutorial/Load scenario beginner tutorial.png]]


9. Follow the in-game tutorial :-)

[[File:en/Manual/Tutorial/BeginnerTutorial.png]]

== Tutorial AI ==
A previous attempt to create a in-game tutorial was TutorialAI that used the AI framework. This AI shows step-by-step instructions, e.g. how to build a bus connection.

This tutorial works also with OpenTTD 1.1.x.

